What is Secrets Manager?
Securely stores sensitive information.

Examples of Secrets:
Database Passwords
API Keys
OAuth Tokens
Application Credentials

Problem Without Secrets Manager:
Developers store passwords inside code.

db_password="admin123"

Security risk.

Correct Approach:
Application
      ↓
Secrets Manager
      ↓
Retrieve Password

Secret Rotation:
Automatically changes credentials.

Example:

Old Password
      ↓
Automatic Rotation
      ↓
New Password

No manual intervention needed.

Real-Time Scenario:

Banking Application

Application
     ↓
Secrets Manager
     ↓
Database Credentials
     ↓
RDS

Passwords never exposed to developers.

